Workers of Trans Mara Medicare Hospital have downed their tools in protest against unpaid salaries.The nurses, clinical officers and accountants at the private hospital say they have not been paid for six months.Spokesman Simon Nyakach said they were last paid in December last year.Speaking in Kilgoris town, Nyakach accused the hospital administration of turning a blind eye to their demands for payment and instead, threatening to sack them. &ldquo;Just like any other Kenyans we have families to take care of and other dependents who look up to us, but every time we ask to be paid we are told to leave,&rdquo; said Nyakach, who is also the Health Records Information Officer. Clinical officer Amos Ondiek accused the management of intimidating the workers who are most outspoken in their demand for better conditions.